{"word":"κάτοιδα","slug":"κάτοιδα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κάτοιδα</b></el> <el><b>-οισθα,</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>-ειδέναι</el>) (<a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>-ειδώς</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a>in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> sense, plup. <el>κατῄδη</el> in <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> sense\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to know well, understand</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to know by sight, recognise</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <el>οὐ κατειδώς</el> <i>unwittingly</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <i>to know well that</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to know how</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}